cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the fundamental task of estimating a depth map from multiple views of a scene, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed approach involves using convolutional neural networks to learn a matching function that maps multiple image patches to a scalar similarity score. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves measuring similarity across multiple image patches, which could place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the experiments involve working with multi-view datasets, which could suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
